ice_US', 'type': 'DMAPPLET', 'description': 'Mapplet calls the Email Web Service to process emails. Email Verification combines state-of-the-art email verification algorithms with hygiene algorithms to allow customers to detect and avoid dangerous or potentially dangerous email addresses or domains. \nNOTE: The user must update the expression asset to include their user ids and passwords or license keys.\n', 'updatedBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'updateTime': '2024-02-20T11:24:28Z', 'tags': ['Y1', 'Z'], 'sourceControl': {'checkedOutBy': None, 'checkedOutTime': None, 'hash': 'e916ae7501424f625bbc911bb1497ea51aede755', 'lastCheckinTime': '2024-02-20T11:31:42Z', 'lastCheckinBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'lastPullTime': None, 'sourceControlled': True}, 'customAttributes': None}, {'id': '0kZTbLokbwSl2B0ScYmqAE', 'path': 'TESTV2/V2/mplt_email_validation_webservice_US', 'type': 'DMAPPLET', 'description': 'Mapplet calls the Email Web Service to process emails. Email Verification combines state-of-the-art email verification algorithms with hygiene algorithms to allow customers to detect and avoid dangerous or potentially dangerous email addresses or domains. \nNOTE: The user must update the expression asset to include their user ids and passwords or license keys.\n', 'updatedBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'updateTime': '2024-02-20T11:39:47Z', 'tags': ['Z'], 'sourceControl': {'checkedOutBy': None, 'checkedOutTime': None, 'hash': 'f4dd886ae0563bc7129349f68fa30ac35be8677e', 'lastCheckinTime': '2024-02-20T11:55:39Z', 'lastCheckinBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'lastPullTime': None, 'sourceControlled': True}, 'customAttributes': None}, {'id': '6gOWl9zZelXjhpa4V2VVAG', 'path': 'Data Quality - Rahul K/mplt_Geocoordinate_In_Polygon', 'type': 'DMAPPLET', 'description': 'Determines if a coordinate point falls inside or outside a set of coordinates that form a polygon shape. Enter the latitude and longitude values for the coordinate point in the Coordinate_Point field. Enter the latitude and longitude values that define the polygon in the Polygon_Coordinates field.\nEnter the latitude and longitude values in decimal format. Use a semi-colon to separate the values. For example:\n17.25458;78.244393\nWhen you enter the polygon coordinates, use a pipe symbol to separate each set of latitude and longitude values. For example:\n88;-179.999999|89.999999;-179.999999|89.999999;179.999999|88;179.999999\nThe polygon coordinates must connect to each other in a sequence that describes the perimeter of the polygon. For example, the first point connects to the second point, and the second point connects to the third point.', 'updatedBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'updateTime': '2024-02-12T07:03:22Z', 'tags': [], 'sourceControl': {'checkedOutBy': None, 'checkedOutTime': None, 'hash': 'ab419ddd78cfa93070e52f887f91719250bbf756', 'lastCheckinTime': '2024-02-12T08:25:17Z', 'lastCheckinBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'lastPullTime': None, 'sourceControlled': True}, 'customAttributes': None}, {'id': '7WR5QfAgC2SbVw5HPUk3k4', 'path': 'Rahul/DQ/mplt_Geocoordinate_In_Polygon', 'type': 'DMAPPLET', 'description': 'Determines if a coordinate point falls inside or outside a set of coordinates that form a polygon shape. Enter the latitude and longitude values for the coordinate point in the Coordinate_Point field. Enter the latitude and longitude values that define the polygon in the Polygon_Coordinates field.\nEnter the latitude and longitude values in decimal format. Use a semi-colon to separate the values. For example:\n17.25458;78.244393\nWhen you enter the polygon coordinates, use a pipe symbol to separate each set of latitude and longitude values. For example:\n88;-179.999999|89.999999;-179.999999|89.999999;179.999999|88;179.999999\nThe polygon coordinates must connect to each other in a sequence that describes the perimeter of the polygon. For example, the first point connects to the second point, and the second point connects to the third point.', 'updatedBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'updateTime': '2024-02-20T11:24:17Z', 'tags': ['Y1', 'Z'], 'sourceControl': {'checkedOutBy': None, 'checkedOutTime': None, 'hash': 'e916ae7501424f625bbc911bb1497ea51aede755', 'lastCheckinTime': '2024-02-20T11:31:42Z', 'lastCheckinBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'lastPullTime': None, 'sourceControlled': True}, 'customAttributes': None}, {'id': '0B6JKNKgKrrlGaai3T78aX', 'path': 'TESTV2/V2/mplt_Geocoordinate_In_Polygon', 'type': 'DMAPPLET', 'description': 'Determines if a coordinate point falls inside or outside a set of coordinates that form a polygon shape. Enter the latitude and longitude values for the coordinate point in the Coordinate_Point field. Enter the latitude and longitude values that define the polygon in the Polygon_Coordinates field.\nEnter the latitude and longitude values in decimal format. Use a semi-colon to separate the values. For example:\n17.25458;78.244393\nWhen you enter the polygon coordinates, use a pipe symbol to separate each set of latitude and longitude values. For example:\n88;-179.999999|89.999999;-179.999999|89.999999;179.999999|88;179.999999\nThe polygon coordinates must connect to each other in a sequence that describes the perimeter of the polygon. For example, the first point connects to the second point, and the second point connects to the third point.', 'updatedBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'updateTime': '2024-02-20T11:39:21Z', 'tags': ['Z'], 'sourceControl': {'checkedOutBy': None, 'checkedOutTime': None, 'hash': 'f4dd886ae0563bc7129349f68fa30ac35be8677e', 'lastCheckinTime': '2024-02-20T11:55:39Z', 'lastCheckinBy': 'CICD_automation_dev', 'lastPullTime': None, 'sourceControlled': True}, 'customAttributes': None}, {'id': '7wu4FDDbzcmkaHf44kdTyB', 'path': 'Data Quality - Rahul K/mplt_Global_Address_Validation_Hybrid', 'type': 'DMAPPLET', 'description': 'Validates the deliverability of address records from multiple countries. The mapplet corrects errors where possible. Use the rule with input address fields in a hybrid format.', 'updatedBy